1
00:00:12,012 --> 00:00:14,304
MINISTRY OF EDUCATION

2
00:00:14,305 --> 00:00:15,681
I checked everywhere,

3
00:00:15,682 --> 00:00:17,850
but no CCTV cameras
cover the rooftop at all.

4
00:00:17,851 --> 00:00:21,437
But one from the next-door building
might capture a small part of it.

5
00:00:21,438 --> 00:00:23,522
Can you explain and show me?

6
00:00:23,523 --> 00:00:24,523
Of course.

7
00:00:24,524 --> 00:00:26,233
The quality is terrible though.

8
00:00:26,234 --> 00:00:28,569
- You can barely make anything out.
- Okay.

9
00:00:28,570 --> 00:00:30,071
- Let's see.
- Yes, sir.

10
00:00:32,615 --> 00:00:33,575
This is it.

11
00:00:34,075 --> 00:00:36,119
- Can you zoom in?
- Yes.

12
00:00:46,504 --> 00:00:48,048
What if someone was here?

13
00:00:49,966 --> 00:00:52,135
What if someone pushed him off?

14
00:01:18,703 --> 00:01:20,288
What brings you here?

15
00:01:20,955 --> 00:01:22,414
Isn't it chaotic at the ERPB?

16
00:01:22,415 --> 00:01:25,126
It's more chaotic in my mind.

17
00:01:27,128 --> 00:01:29,755
I'm wondering
why you came back to this school,

18
00:01:29,756 --> 00:01:31,965
reported bullying as soon as you arrived,

19
00:01:31,966 --> 00:01:34,677
and are doing this now.

20
00:01:39,182 --> 00:01:40,433
Have you done your homework?

21
00:01:44,604 --> 00:01:45,438
Oh, sorry.

22
00:01:46,022 --> 00:01:47,398
I sounded like a salesperson.

23
00:01:48,191 --> 00:01:49,984
If you know what's going on,

24
00:01:50,485 --> 00:01:51,694
I can tell you everything.

25
00:01:52,737 --> 00:01:55,197
I know you want the ERPB gone.

26
00:01:55,198 --> 00:01:56,533
And why would that be?

27
00:02:02,122 --> 00:02:03,498
Probably because of this.

28
00:02:07,168 --> 00:02:09,712
Heart Pills most recently.
Butterfly Pills two years ago.

29
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:11,964
What are they now?

30
00:02:11,965 --> 00:02:13,591
Diamond.

31
00:02:15,260 --> 00:02:16,885
I guess you don't have any proof.

32
00:02:16,886 --> 00:02:19,680
Otherwise, you'd have called the police
or arrested me.

33
00:02:19,681 --> 00:02:21,975
But here you are, chatting away with me.

34
00:02:24,602 --> 00:02:27,021
You and Ms. Choi

35
00:02:27,522 --> 00:02:29,566
were made for each other.

36
00:02:30,066 --> 00:02:32,985
You're so alike, sticking your nose
in other people's business.

37
00:02:32,986 --> 00:02:35,572
I wonder if you'll share the same fate.

38
00:02:48,334 --> 00:02:49,335
Hey.

39
00:02:49,836 --> 00:02:52,212
Why are you here?
I said I'm not coming to school.

40
00:02:52,213 --> 00:02:53,380
You punk.

41
00:02:53,381 --> 00:02:56,592
Did you expect me to just say,
"Okay, sure, take care"?

42
00:02:56,593 --> 00:02:58,177
That wouldn't do.

43
00:02:58,178 --> 00:03:00,180
Hey, wait. Come here.

44
00:03:00,847 --> 00:03:03,682
Every time you skip school,
you're injured like this.

45
00:03:03,683 --> 00:03:06,226
Oh, that looks pretty bad.

46
00:03:06,227 --> 00:03:08,145
- Let me put some cream on it.
- I'm fine.

47
00:03:08,146 --> 00:03:09,647
Just stay still.

48
00:03:12,275 --> 00:03:13,276
Let's see this side.

49
00:03:14,027 --> 00:03:16,737
I don't know what you've been up to,

50
00:03:16,738 --> 00:03:18,739
but do it at school.

51
00:03:18,740 --> 00:03:20,408
It's the safest place, okay?

52
00:03:20,909 --> 00:03:22,784
The safest place? Since when?

53
00:03:22,785 --> 00:03:24,536
It's not just me.

54
00:03:24,537 --> 00:03:26,872
Lots of teachers
are trying to make it safe.

55
00:03:26,873 --> 00:03:29,542
We'll make school a safe place. I promise.

56
00:03:30,460 --> 00:03:32,003
Here, promise.

57
00:03:34,047 --> 00:03:35,548
That's how you break a finger.

58
00:03:37,675 --> 00:03:38,801
You little punk.

59
00:03:39,385 --> 00:03:41,220
Fine, don't come. I won't either.

60
00:03:41,221 --> 00:03:43,972
I'll follow you around forever.
You think I'm bluffing?

61
00:03:43,973 --> 00:03:46,058
You know what my boyfriend calls me?

62
00:03:46,059 --> 00:03:49,311
Flypaper.
Once I catch you, I never let go.

63
00:03:49,312 --> 00:03:52,357
I'm coming to pick you up
tomorrow morning. Got it?

64
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:08,830
Hey, Gyu-cheol. Good morning.

65
00:04:08,831 --> 00:04:11,416
Hey, come on. Breakfast...

66
00:04:11,417 --> 00:04:12,794
Gyu-cheol.

67
00:04:14,504 --> 00:04:16,505
Wait. Oh, come on.

68
00:04:16,506 --> 00:04:17,756
- Cho Gyu-cheol.
- Yes?

69
00:04:17,757 --> 00:04:19,341
I'm his homeroom teacher.

70
00:04:19,342 --> 00:04:20,968
You're students, right?

71
00:04:20,969 --> 00:04:22,387
- Put that out.
- Fucking hell.

72
00:04:23,846 --> 00:04:24,972
Gyu-cheol, come on.

73
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:26,014
- Let's go.
- See you.

74
00:04:26,015 --> 00:04:27,517
- Don't look.
- We'll call you.

75
00:04:42,699 --> 00:04:44,826
Hey, what the hell are you thinking?

76
00:04:45,326 --> 00:04:48,495
The Samgeori guys who came at you
are now after your ass.

77
00:04:48,496 --> 00:04:50,623
Are you seeing that bitch, Choi Ga-yun?

78
00:04:52,709 --> 00:04:55,253
Do you know what Ms. Choi made me realize?

79
00:04:56,629 --> 00:04:59,339
The school is full of people.

80
00:04:59,340 --> 00:05:01,258
So? What about it?

81
00:05:01,259 --> 00:05:03,885
Imagine they were all customers.

82
00:05:03,886 --> 00:05:04,928
- Get inside.
- Nice.

83
00:05:04,929 --> 00:05:09,225
It'd be easy to dodge the cops
and move the product back and forth.

84
00:05:09,934 --> 00:05:11,518
Best of all,

85
00:05:11,519 --> 00:05:14,981
we'd get hundreds of new customers
every year.

86
00:05:22,989 --> 00:05:23,905
Oh man, it's cold.

87
00:05:23,906 --> 00:05:24,824
Ms. Choi.

88
00:05:29,245 --> 00:05:30,162
Gyu-cheol.

89
00:05:30,163 --> 00:05:31,706
You're in uniform.

90
00:05:32,582 --> 00:05:35,000
I figured I'd come to school properly now.

91
00:05:35,001 --> 00:05:36,918
Hey, that's a great decision.

92
00:05:36,919 --> 00:05:39,130
That's a good boy.

93
00:05:40,715 --> 00:05:43,342
I won't touch your hair
since you have your own style.

94
00:05:43,343 --> 00:05:46,346
You haven't eaten, have you?
Want to grab some <i>gimbap</i>?

95
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:17,668
I BELIEVE IN YOU, GYU-CHEOL!

96
00:06:34,727 --> 00:06:36,937
If she'd just turned a blind eye
back then,

97
00:06:36,938 --> 00:06:39,481
you two would be married by now.

98
00:06:39,482 --> 00:06:40,400
Right?

99
00:06:47,115 --> 00:06:49,826
What's that for?
You're not gonna hit me, are you?

100
00:06:54,705 --> 00:06:56,082
You shouldn't do that.

101
00:06:56,666 --> 00:06:58,959
There's already a stir
about excessive punishment.

102
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:01,378
If you hit me now,

103
00:07:01,379 --> 00:07:03,131
it'd be a real personal vendetta.

104
00:07:06,426 --> 00:07:08,135
So don't make a move.

105
00:07:08,136 --> 00:07:11,431
If you don't do anything,
nothing will happen--

106
00:07:19,730 --> 00:07:20,898
I'm sorry, Inspector.

107
00:07:21,566 --> 00:07:22,692
I was wrong.

108
00:07:23,276 --> 00:07:24,776
I'm really sorry.

109
00:07:24,777 --> 00:07:27,154
I'm really sorry, Inspector.
Please spare me.

110
00:07:27,155 --> 00:07:29,073
I'm sorry.

111
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:31,367
I was wrong.

112
00:07:31,868 --> 00:07:33,452
Please spare me just this once.

113
00:07:33,453 --> 00:07:35,454
Please. I'm sorry!

114
00:07:35,455 --> 00:07:37,373
TEACH YOU A LESSON

115
00:07:38,332 --> 00:07:39,749
<i>I'm really sorry.</i>

116
00:07:39,750 --> 00:07:42,753
<i>I'm really sorry, Inspector.
Please spare me.</i>

117
00:07:43,379 --> 00:07:45,338
This is exactly
what I was concerned about.

118
00:07:45,339 --> 00:07:46,715
Only a few days ago,

119
00:07:46,716 --> 00:07:49,426
excessive punishment
drove Lee Chi-ho to attempt suicide.

120
00:07:49,427 --> 00:07:52,387
Now, Cho Gyu-cheol, doing well at school,
has been assaulted.

121
00:07:52,388 --> 00:07:54,139
Why do you think this happened?

122
00:07:54,140 --> 00:07:55,974
The ERPB went to Jinwon High,

123
00:07:55,975 --> 00:07:58,478
<i>targeting Cho Gyu-cheol from the start.</i>

124
00:07:59,479 --> 00:08:01,480
<i>They went there for personal revenge,</i>

125
00:08:01,481 --> 00:08:04,484
<i>looking for an excuse to harass him.</i>

126
00:08:05,193 --> 00:08:06,277
<i>In the end,</i>

127
00:08:06,986 --> 00:08:09,906
<i>it was Lee Chi-ho who was sacrificed.</i>

128
00:08:10,656 --> 00:08:12,658
I won't stand by and allow such cruelty.

129
00:08:13,242 --> 00:08:18,247
I will see to it that the ERPB,
fueled by personal revenge, is dismantled.

130
00:08:19,790 --> 00:08:21,750
<i>With opinion polls</i>

131
00:08:21,751 --> 00:08:26,463
<i>showing that more than 50% of the public
support disbanding the ERPB,</i>

132
00:08:26,464 --> 00:08:29,049
<i>the president
is under considerable pressure</i>

133
00:08:29,050 --> 00:08:31,469
<i>during the lame-duck period of his term.</i>

134
00:08:31,969 --> 00:08:34,971
<i>Despite strong resistance
from the opposition party,</i>

135
00:08:34,972 --> 00:08:37,641
<i>the president
has so far kept the ERPB in place.</i>

136
00:08:37,642 --> 00:08:39,643
<i>- But his approval rating is at 20%.</i>
- Hello?

137
00:08:39,644 --> 00:08:42,437
<i>To navigate this
and bring his term to a steady close...</i>

138
00:08:42,438 --> 00:08:44,315
I'll come see you now.

139
00:08:46,567 --> 00:08:47,985
It's the ERPB!

140
00:08:56,452 --> 00:08:58,203
What are you doing here?

141
00:08:58,204 --> 00:09:00,330
The ERPB shouldn't come
to schools anymore.

142
00:09:00,331 --> 00:09:04,167
We're neither potential criminals
nor targets of personal revenge.

143
00:09:04,168 --> 00:09:06,378
I'm here to investigate Lee Chi-ho's case.

144
00:09:06,379 --> 00:09:09,172
Why would the ERPB investigate

145
00:09:09,173 --> 00:09:11,716
when they caused
Chi-ho to end up like that?

146
00:09:11,717 --> 00:09:15,221
Do you really think
you can conduct a fair investigation?

147
00:09:25,898 --> 00:09:27,857
<i>The ERPB's duties will be suspended</i>

148
00:09:27,858 --> 00:09:32,070
<i>until the investigation
into the student's suicide attempt</i>

149
00:09:32,071 --> 00:09:34,031
at Jinwon High School

150
00:09:34,949 --> 00:09:36,117
is concluded.

151
00:09:37,618 --> 00:09:38,577
Accordingly,

152
00:09:38,578 --> 00:09:41,122
<i>the duties of the ERPB inspectors</i>

153
00:09:41,831 --> 00:09:42,748
<i>will be suspended.</i>

154
00:09:51,090 --> 00:09:53,593
DEPUTY DIRECTOR BONG GEUN-DAE
ERPB

155
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:36,052
Hey.

156
00:10:36,927 --> 00:10:39,220
Everything is set.
When do we start selling?

157
00:10:39,221 --> 00:10:41,807
Now that the ERPB's out of the way,
we can get started.

158
00:10:42,642 --> 00:10:44,935
First, send samples
to each school's main dealer.

159
00:10:46,604 --> 00:10:48,355
Have them drum up business with those.

160
00:10:48,356 --> 00:10:51,650
Tell them
once a school hits over 100 customers,

161
00:10:51,651 --> 00:10:54,444
we'll start the drop for real.

162
00:10:54,445 --> 00:10:57,281
We'll need a shitload of runners.
Just us isn't enough.

163
00:10:58,699 --> 00:11:01,451
Schools aren't just full of customers.

164
00:11:01,452 --> 00:11:03,203
They've got runners too.

165
00:11:03,204 --> 00:11:05,164
And they're all minors.

166
00:11:05,665 --> 00:11:07,792
No one suspects students.

167
00:11:08,292 --> 00:11:11,212
And even if they get caught,
they'll get out right away.

168
00:11:11,712 --> 00:11:13,214
Best of all,

169
00:11:13,714 --> 00:11:15,341
they're disposable.

170
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:27,353
I flip sneakers with this guy
for some pocket money.

171
00:11:28,020 --> 00:11:29,729
But there are so many scams

172
00:11:29,730 --> 00:11:32,650
that people want to check them out
in person.

173
00:11:34,568 --> 00:11:36,654
All you have to do is deliver them.

174
00:11:39,824 --> 00:11:40,658
Okay.

175
00:11:46,664 --> 00:11:47,831
Hey.

176
00:11:47,832 --> 00:11:49,834
Oh, hello.

177
00:11:51,460 --> 00:11:53,837
SOYEON GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

178
00:11:53,838 --> 00:11:55,131
They're the right ones.

179
00:12:02,179 --> 00:12:03,389
Yeah, it checks out.

180
00:12:04,348 --> 00:12:05,182
Here.

181
00:12:05,891 --> 00:12:07,809
How was it? Easy, right?

182
00:12:07,810 --> 00:12:08,811
Wanna do it again?

183
00:12:09,770 --> 00:12:10,812
Can I?

184
00:12:10,813 --> 00:12:13,149
If you do, that would be great.

185
00:12:20,072 --> 00:12:22,073
- Hello.
- You're here.

186
00:12:22,074 --> 00:12:23,116
- Gyu-cheol.
- Hey.

187
00:12:23,117 --> 00:12:24,200
You're here.

188
00:12:24,201 --> 00:12:25,786
Go on.

189
00:12:35,004 --> 00:12:36,797
Thanks. Can't wait to wear them.

190
00:12:51,061 --> 00:12:53,313
It's called biodiversity.

191
00:12:53,314 --> 00:12:56,024
There's genetic diversity,
species diversity,

192
00:12:56,025 --> 00:12:57,610
ecosystem diversity...

193
00:12:58,360 --> 00:13:01,029
Jin-hyeok and Ju-won, focus.

194
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:05,366
Traits within the same species
are determined by genetic information.

195
00:13:05,367 --> 00:13:09,370
So what do we call the part of DNA
that stores this information?

196
00:13:09,371 --> 00:13:11,207
We call it genes.

197
00:13:12,124 --> 00:13:15,169
We're in the middle of class.
What's with everyone today?

198
00:13:15,669 --> 00:13:17,046
Let's all focus.

199
00:13:19,632 --> 00:13:20,924
- Looks good.
- Right?

200
00:13:20,925 --> 00:13:23,218
Hey, is this art class or what?

201
00:13:23,219 --> 00:13:25,262
You're going all out with the brushes.

202
00:13:26,013 --> 00:13:27,597
You don't need this, do you?

203
00:13:27,598 --> 00:13:29,474
You're so pretty with a petite face.

204
00:13:29,475 --> 00:13:30,767
So jealous.

205
00:13:30,768 --> 00:13:33,479
Thanks, but I used to have a big face

206
00:13:34,063 --> 00:13:35,230
like you two.

207
00:13:35,231 --> 00:13:38,275
- Sorry. I actually just lost some weight.
- Really?

208
00:13:39,151 --> 00:13:40,569
What kind of diet was it?

209
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:42,196
I took pills.

210
00:13:43,823 --> 00:13:45,407
They're hard to get.

211
00:13:46,075 --> 00:13:47,951
Try them, and if they work, let me know.

212
00:13:47,952 --> 00:13:49,661
- Thanks.
- You sure I can have these?

213
00:13:49,662 --> 00:13:51,412
- Yeah.
- This is crazy.

214
00:13:51,413 --> 00:13:52,997
<i>Pitch done.</i>

215
00:13:52,998 --> 00:13:55,334
<i>I need more samples. Please send them.</i>

216
00:13:56,460 --> 00:13:57,293
Oh, ma'am. I--

217
00:13:57,294 --> 00:13:59,838
Oh, Seong-gu.
Seong-jun was in a motorcycle accident.

218
00:13:59,839 --> 00:14:02,883
I have to go to the hospital,
so tell the class to self-study.

219
00:14:05,177 --> 00:14:09,013
Seong-jun got badly hurt
in a motorcycle accident.

220
00:14:09,014 --> 00:14:11,016
Our teacher's gone to the hospital.

221
00:14:12,935 --> 00:14:14,310
Holy shit!

222
00:14:14,311 --> 00:14:17,355
Seong-jun's been delivering like crazy
and actually bought a bike.

223
00:14:17,356 --> 00:14:19,358
Fuck, really? Let me see.

224
00:14:20,693 --> 00:14:22,443
- Let me see.
- What is it? Show me too.

225
00:14:22,444 --> 00:14:23,862
- Get lost.
- Hey, wait.

226
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:26,197
- I'm a fucking genius.
- Why?

227
00:14:26,198 --> 00:14:28,950
We can just take over
that punk Seong-jun's routes. Right?

228
00:14:28,951 --> 00:14:30,119
Right?

229
00:14:32,288 --> 00:14:33,580
- True.
- We're pros.

230
00:14:33,581 --> 00:14:35,874
<i>Doesn't it feel off in school lately?</i>

231
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:39,586
More kids are absent or leaving early,
and everyone seems kind of distracted.

232
00:14:39,587 --> 00:14:41,421
I'm so scared of kids these days.

233
00:14:41,422 --> 00:14:42,964
When the ERPB was around,

234
00:14:42,965 --> 00:14:46,342
I didn't exactly feel respected,
but I did feel protected.

235
00:14:46,343 --> 00:14:48,929
It feels like we're back
to how things used to be.

236
00:14:57,563 --> 00:14:58,981
LOOKING FOR ADHD MEDS
OK, CAN DO

237
00:15:01,483 --> 00:15:02,400
NEED BEAUTY PILLS

238
00:15:02,401 --> 00:15:04,320
Wow, fucking hell.

239
00:15:05,738 --> 00:15:10,116
We have about 17 schools in Seoul alone,
with roughly 100 orders from each.

240
00:15:10,117 --> 00:15:12,369
Looks like
all that sample-pushing paid off.

241
00:15:17,416 --> 00:15:19,167
Let's start selling for real today.

242
00:15:19,168 --> 00:15:21,921
Then should I blast it out
on Telegram right now?

243
00:15:23,464 --> 00:15:24,840
CHO GYU-CHEOL
DROP IT ONCE PAID

244
00:15:27,468 --> 00:15:29,637
DROP IT ONCE PAID

245
00:15:45,986 --> 00:15:47,821
Can I go to the nurse's office?

246
00:15:49,031 --> 00:15:51,449
Ma'am, I've got a terrible headache too.

247
00:15:51,450 --> 00:15:55,120
Ma'am, I'm really sorry,
but my stomach hurts so much. Excuse me.

248
00:15:57,456 --> 00:15:58,582
Ma'am.

249
00:15:59,166 --> 00:16:03,671
Well, my grandma is really sick,
so I've got to rush home now.

250
00:16:04,171 --> 00:16:05,422
I'll see you tomorrow.

251
00:16:07,383 --> 00:16:08,384
Damn it.

252
00:16:15,224 --> 00:16:16,433
Hey, I'm coming too.

253
00:16:23,732 --> 00:16:24,858
Hey, Seong-gu.

254
00:16:25,359 --> 00:16:26,986
I saved one for you.

255
00:16:27,611 --> 00:16:28,445
Here.

256
